Spain's Emilio Sanchez continued his  disappointing recent run of results when he was beaten in three sets by  American Bryan Shelton of the United States in the first round of the 300,000  dollar ATP tournament here on Tuesday.
The 6ft 1in Atlanta player scored a 7-6 (7/4), 4-6, 6-3 win.
1st round results (x-denotes seeded player):
Marc Goellner (Germany x7) bt Francisco Clavet (Spain) 2-6, 6-3, 6-4
Andrea Gaudenzi (Italy x4) bt Carl Uwe Steeb (Germany) 6-1, 2-6, 6-4
Slava Dosedel (Czech x6) bt Franco Davin (Argentina) 4-6, 6-2, 6-2
Jordi Burrillo (Spain) bt Karim Alami (Mor) 6-4, 6-3
Brian Shelton (USA) bt Emilio Sanchez (Spain) 7-6 (7/4), 4-6, 6-3
Kenneth Carlsen (Denmark) bt Omar Camporese (Italy) 6-1, 6-2.
